HEADWORD: Water chevrotain
<hw>Wa"ter chev`ro*tain"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large West African chevrotain (<spn>Hyaemoschus aquaticus</spn>). It has
a larger body and shorter legs than the other allied species. Called
also <altname>water deerlet</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water chicken</ent>⟦br⟧
